06:47:41.440 --> 06:47:43.910
reward a few times.

06:47:43.920 --> 06:47:45.390
And then they have to learn something

06:47:45.400 --> 06:47:48.430
based on that.

06:47:51.750 --> 06:47:51.760
With the state set algorithm though,

06:47:51.760 --> 06:47:53.670
as soon as you get the reward,

06:47:53.680 --> 06:47:55.110
you will trigger a high advantage

06:47:55.120 --> 06:47:56.630
estimate, right?

06:47:56.640 --> 06:47:58.270
Cuz you expected to get no reward cuz

06:47:58.280 --> 06:48:00.150
all you've ever seen is no reward, you

06:48:00.160 --> 06:48:01.470
get a big reward, you have a big

06:48:01.480 --> 06:48:03.430
advantage estimate.

06:48:03.440 --> 06:48:06.710
You can use this to automatically save

06:48:06.720 --> 06:48:09.230
a bunch of the states leading up to

06:48:09.240 --> 06:48:10.830
getting the reward,

06:48:10.840 --> 06:48:12.670
store them in a buffer, and then you can

06:48:12.680 --> 06:48:15.670
sample those as starting states.

06:48:15.680 --> 06:48:17.230
This is fully general. I'm not

06:48:17.240 --> 06:48:19.190
exploiting any property whatsoever of

06:48:19.200 --> 06:48:21.630
the maze, of the reward structure, fully

06:48:21.640 --> 06:48:23.070
fully general. It doesn't need to be

06:48:23.080 --> 06:48:27.630
deterministic, nothing.

06:48:29.070 --> 06:48:29.080
And then essentially you get yourself

06:48:29.080 --> 06:48:31.350
some very nice start states that are

06:48:31.360 --> 06:48:33.070
close to a reward.

06:48:33.080 --> 06:48:34.310
Maybe you don't get the reward every

06:48:34.320 --> 06:48:36.790
time from the same start states, right?

06:48:36.800 --> 06:48:38.870
But like it's a way easier exploration

06:48:38.880 --> 06:48:41.190
problem now.

06:48:41.200 --> 06:48:43.630
And then once you get some more rewards,

06:48:43.640 --> 06:48:45.470
you can put those into the buffer and it

06:48:45.480 --> 06:48:54.630
accumulates very quickly from there.

06:48:57.110 --> 06:48:57.120
Um so this is I like I believe this is a

06:48:57.120 --> 06:48:58.870
major breakthrough

06:48:58.880 --> 06:49:01.950
because this latching problem has

06:49:01.960 --> 06:49:04.310
plagued me for years. I have never had a

06:49:04.320 --> 06:49:06.830
way to solve this problem ever.

06:49:06.840 --> 06:49:08.910
Now look, as Puffer has gotten better,

06:49:08.920 --> 06:49:10.430
it's been able to solve harder and

06:49:10.440 --> 06:49:12.710
harder exploration problems.

06:49:12.720 --> 06:49:15.310
Um but this is a very large jump, I

06:49:15.320 --> 06:49:17.470
think. I think this is a very large

06:49:17.480 --> 06:49:19.590
jump. I'm not going to know whether this

06:49:19.600 --> 06:49:21.990
is a very large jump until I fully go

06:49:22.000 --> 06:49:24.590
run some sweeps.

06:49:24.600 --> 06:49:26.950
I think it would be very very surprising

06:49:26.960 --> 06:49:29.430
though if you can solve this with any

06:49:29.440 --> 06:49:32.550
other method, particularly because I'm

06:49:32.560 --> 06:49:34.310
going to start sweeping this up a little

06:49:34.320 --> 06:49:36.710
bit.

06:49:36.720 --> 06:49:38.030
And um

06:49:38.040 --> 06:49:38.990
you know, I'm going to start sweeping

06:49:39.000 --> 06:49:41.070
this upwards and we're going to see what

06:49:41.080 --> 06:49:43.870
the hardest one you can solve is with

06:49:43.880 --> 06:49:45.550
the new curriculum method with better

06:49:45.560 --> 06:49:47.670
parameters and then we'll see the same

06:49:47.680 --> 06:49:53.230
thing for the standard algorithm.

06:50:06.590 --> 06:50:06.600
You're basically just sampling states

06:50:06.600 --> 06:50:09.310
that have high advantage.

06:50:09.320 --> 06:50:10.510
And then you're setting the state of

06:50:10.520 --> 06:50:11.990
some of your environments to those

06:50:12.000 --> 06:50:15.390
samples.

06:50:17.270 --> 06:50:17.280
So, it's funny that like this can kind

06:50:17.280 --> 06:50:19.350
of do a search implicitly,

06:50:19.360 --> 06:50:27.110
but this is not a search method.

